in SpringCloudConfigServer project

in application.properties add
-----------------------------
spring.application.name=config-server
server.port=8888
 
for local git repository
#spring.cloud.config.server.git.uri=file:///f:/config-properties

for remote Git
spring.cloud.config.server.git.uri=https://github.com/ranaraghu1/restapi


In spring cloud latest version,2020 and later version add below dependency

<dependency>
    		<groupId>org.springframework.cloud</groupId>
    		<artifactId>spring-cloud-starter-bootstrap</artifactId>
</dependency>

in SpringBoot application class/main class-- add  @EnableConfigServer
-------------------------------------------------------------
@EnableConfigServer
@SpringBootApplication
public class SpringCloudConfigServerApplication {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		SpringApplication.run(SpringCloudConfigServerApplication.class, args);
	}

}


to test this-  http://localhost:8888/product-service/dev/

               http://localhost:8888/product-service/default/
               
               
 create file below file in git repository
 product-service.properties ,     product-service-dev.properties
               
               
 Create a client App to get default and dev configuration
 --------------------------------------------------------
 Add following properties in pom.xml file
 
      <dependency>
			<groupId>org.springframework.cloud</groupId>
			<artifactId>spring-cloud-starter-config</artifactId>
		</dependency>
		
 in application.properties file rename to bootstarp.properties
 
 add add following properties
 
spring.application.name=product-service
spring.cloud.config.uri=http://localhost:8888

if want to activate Dev or QA profile add spring.profiles.active=dev
 
 
 
               
               
               
               